Velocity consumes data from third-party upstream feeds, EACH UNDER ITS OWN
LICENSE AND TERMS. The code license does not relicense that data. Before any
commercial or redistributive use, verify each upstream's CURRENT terms — some
prohibit commercial use outright.

Notable upstreams and their terms (non-exhaustive; verify before relying on):

- ACLED (acleddata.com) — non-commercial / academic; attribution required.
- adsb.fi, airplanes.live, adsb.lol — community ADS-B; non-commercial terms.
- OpenSky Network — research / non-commercial; attribution required.
- NASA FIRMS, EONET, GIBS — NASA open data; attribution appreciated.
- USGS earthquakes; NOAA SWPC — US Government public domain.
- EMSC / seismicportal.eu — attribution.
- GDELT Project — open; attribution.
- Digitraffic (Fintraffic) — CC BY 4.0.
- Kystverket / Kystdatahuset (Norway) — open government data.
- Global Fishing Watch — API terms; attribution; non-commercial tiers.
- Copernicus / Sentinel via CDSE — free, full and open (Copernicus license).
- CelesTrak — public GP/TLE data.
- OpenStreetMap / Overpass / Nominatim — ODbL; usage policies apply.
- CARTO basemaps; Esri ArcGIS World Imagery — provider TOS / basemap terms.
- TeleGeography Submarine Cable Map — attribution.
- Wikipedia / Wikidata — CC BY-SA.
- News RSS (BBC, NPR, Sky News, Fox, CNN, DW, The Guardian, Al Jazeera,
  France 24, CNBC, Google News) — headlines and links indexed for fair use;
  full article content remains the property of the respective publishers.

The live `/api/intel/sources` endpoint reports which feeds are active, which are
key-gated, and which are degraded from the current egress.
